HEADWORD: micro-chemistry
<hw>mi`cro-chem"is*try</hw></mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Micro-</ets> +
<ets>chemistry</ets>.]</ety> <def>The application of chemical tests to
minute objects or portions of matter, usually assisted by sensitive
instruments; -- distinguished from <xex>macro-chemistry</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

